.TH simple_shell 1 "May 2026" "simple_shell man-page"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBsimple_shell\fP is a simple UNIX command line interpreter written in C
for Holberton School. It reads commands from the user and executes them.
It works in both interactive and non-interactive mode. It also handles the \fBPATH\fP environment variable to resolve commands.
.SH USAGE
.SS Interactive mode
The shell displays a prompt and waits for the user to type a command.
.PP
$ ./hsh
.PP
($) ls
.PP
hsh main.c shell.c shell.h
.PP
($)
.SS Non-interactive mode
The shell can also receive commands from a pipe or a file.
.PP
$ echo "ls" | ./hsh
.PP
hsh main.c shell.c shell.h
.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
The following built-in commands are supported:
.TP
\fBenv\fP
Prints the current environment variables.
.TP
\fBexit\fP
Exits the shell with the status of the last executed command.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Upon success, the command returns 0.
If a command is not found, \fB127\fP is returned.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
($) ls
.PP
Output: lists files in current directory
.PP
($) pwd
.PP
Output: prints current working directory
.PP
($) echo Hello
.PP
Output: Hello
.SH AUTHORS
Written by Noura Alotibi and Mohammed Mustafa as part of the Holberton School simple shell project.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR fork (2),
.BR waitpid (2),
.BR getline (3)
.SH NOTES
This implementation is a simplified version of the standard shell.
